The paper proposes a framework for program repair, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The approach involves symbolic execution and logic specifications, which are topics in programming languages (cs.PL) and formal methods (cs.LO). The iterative refinement loop and lazy candidate repair selection suggest the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with control-flow paths, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
